      Initializes this Sidebar and associated components and functionality..

    • getButtonBox

      public javafx.scene.layout.VBox getButtonBox()

      Returns the VBox container housing all selection buttons mapped to all UINodes in this SidebarNodeGroup.

      Details

      1. The VBox returned by this method is created automatically in the SidebarNodeGroup constructor.

      Usage in Sidebar

      1. The Sidebar class automatically sets the button box that is displayed on the UI at any given time to always reflect the selected SidebarNodeGroup.
      2. Therefore, the parent of the VBox returned by this method must never be directly modified, changed, or otherwise manipulated.
      3. This method previously had protected access for that very reason, and was only changed to permit universal read access to the button box.
      Returns:
      The VBox container housing all selection buttons mapped to all UINodes in this SidebarNodeGroup.
      See Also:
      Sidebar.selectedNodeGroupProperty()

    • getButtonGroup

      public BoundImageButtonGroup<UINode> getButtonGroup()

      Returns the BoundImageButtonGroup responsible for containing and managing the ImageButtons used to switch between selected UINodes in this SidebarNodeGroup.

      Details

      1. The BoundImageButtonGroup returned by this method is used for managing UINode selection.
      2. The above works because UINode implements ButtonViewable.
      3. BoundButtonViewGroups add functionality that allows you to retrieve the ButtonViewable (in this case, UINode) the specified ImageButton is assigned to.
      4. The value returned by this method is guaranteed to be non-null.
      Returns:
      The ImageButtonGroup responsible for containing and managing the ImageButtons used to switch between selected UINodes in this SidebarNodeGroup.
      1. Guaranteed to be non-null.
